      "id": "PopularPost201024",
      "post_content": "I think it's funny how the oracle text allows you to use the pre-m10 combat damage rules. Because this card wouldn't be half as good if you have to use the post rules.  \n  \n(those who don't know, when you multi block now the attacking player decided the order he's creature will \"fight\" you're blockers. He then deals combat damage in order, doing at least leathale dmg to each creature before being able to move to the next one. Making things like post combat [Pyroclasim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroclasim) mush less effective.   \nHow ever with pre-m10 combat rules you could divided the damage in any way that you saw fit between the blocking creatures.)",
      "posted_by": "StagemasterK",
